### unknown-subcommand
argv:   acetone st
status: 2
stderr: error: unrecognized subcommand 'st'

  tip: some similar subcommands exist: 'list-nodes', 'status'

Usage: acetone [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

For more information, try '--help'.

### missing-colon-label
argv:   acetone query CREATE (Topic {name: 'First'});
status: 1
stderr: error: cannot persist node: a node with labels [] has no label declaring a key; identity is undefined (Invariant #3)

### schema-not-declared
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Widget {sku: 'a'});
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 8: unknown label 'Widget' at bytes 7..27 (declared labels come from the schema map)

### parse-error
argv:   acetone query MATCH (n) RETRUN n
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 11: expected a clause (MATCH, OPTIONAL MATCH, UNWIND, WITH, RETURN, CALL, CREATE, SET, REMOVE, DELETE or DETACH DELETE), found 'RETRUN' at bytes 10..16

### rel-missing-colon
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'a'})-[LINK]->(:Topic {name: 'b'});
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 28: CREATE requires exactly one relationship type at bytes 27..36

### duplicate-key
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'x'});
status: 1
stderr: error: CREATE of "Topic" "[String(\"x\")]" conflicts with an existing node; identity must be unique (use MERGE to upsert)

### get-node-not-found
argv:   acetone get-node Topic missing
status: 0
stdout: not found
